  Under the influence of intensified sector wage 
differentiation, the level of wages in the fuel industry and 
electric power industry in 1993 being triple the wages in light 
industry and machine building (in 1991 the factor increase was 
1.5- to 1.7-fold), an intersector modulation of numbers of 
employees is taking place. This is increasing appreciably in the 
electric power industry and fuel industry, and decreasing in the 
lumber, woodworking, and pulp and paper industry. 

